HEADWORD: Gadoid
<hw>Ga"doid</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[NL.
<ets>gadus</ets> cod + <ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F. <ets>gado⟦ium⟧de</ets>
gadoid, Gr. <?/ a sort of fish, F. <ets>gade</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the family of fishes
(<fam>Gadid⟦ae⟧</fam>) which includes the cod, haddock, and hake.</def>
-- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>One of the
<fam>Gadid⟦ae⟧</fam>.</def></def2> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>gadid</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gadolinia</ent>⟦br⟧
